    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - DRIVETRAIN FAILURE ANALYSIS - CLUTCH COMPONENTS - RELEASE
        FORK
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="2">
        <title>RELEASE FORK</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Release fork bridge contacting the cover assembly (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300237">Figure 37</hotlnk>). Inspect for the following causes:
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300237" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300237" filename="../figg13/G1300237.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 37. Release Fork Bridge Contacting Cover Assembly</caption>
            </figure>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Worn clutch brake.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Broken or missing clutch brake.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Worn or incorrect transmission bearing cap.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Excessive wear on release bearing housing wear pads.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Excessive wear on release fork fingers.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Incorrect linkage adjustment.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Incorrect release fork.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Machined too much material from the flywheel.</para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Worn fork fingers (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300238">Figure 38</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300238" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300238" filename="../figg13/G1300238.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 38. Worn Fork Fingers</caption>
            </figure>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Failure to maintain free pedal.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Driver abuse by riding the clutch pedal.</para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
